{
  "texts": [
    "• No data adaptation (DA off), i.e., simply streaming data from clients at a prede- fined fixed size.",
    "Specifically, we choose the input size of the middle DNN, i.e., 354 × 354, which provides a good tradeoff between bandwidth requirement and accuracy.",
    "Here, the scheduler knows the data size and treats it as a constant during DNN adaptation.",
    "• Default data adaptation (DA bw) with typical network bandwidth awareness to maintain stable network throughput (Zhang et al. 2018a).",
    "Here, the current network condition is considered but no knowledge about the DNN adaptation component is provided."
  ]
}